The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, which are typically categorized under cs.IT. The use of Gaussian distributions and noise in the MAC system suggests that it may also fall under cs.MM (multimedia), while the consideration of interference and cancellation could place it under cs.NI (networking and internet). The use of encoders and decoders could also suggest cs.SI (signal and image processing), and the study of capacity regions and optimization techniques could fall under cs.CC (computational complexity).
